        "fullLyrics": "[00:31.342] It's nine o'clock on a Saturday\n[00:36.373] The regular crowd shuffles in\n[00:39.434] There's an old man sittin' next to me\n[00:43.534] Makin' love to his tonic and gin\n[00:57.935] He says \"Son can you play me a memory\n[01:01.846] I'm not really sure how it goes\n[01:06.092] But it's sad and it's sweet and I knew it complete\n[01:10.516] When I wore a younger man's clothes\"\n[01:14.364] La la-la di-dee-da\n[01:19.628] La-la di-dee-da da-dum\n[01:26.981] Sing us a song you're the piano man\n[01:30.963] Sing us a song tonight\n[01:34.715] Well we're all in the mood for a melody\n[01:38.557] And you've got us feeling alright\n[01:57.073] Now John at the bar is a friend of mine\n[02:01.336] He gets me my drinks for free\n[02:05.216] And he's quick with a joke or to light up your smoke\n[02:08.717] But there's someplace that he'd rather be\n[02:14.686] He says \"Bill I believe this is killing me\"\n[02:19.038] As the smile ran away from his face\n[02:23.150] \"Well I'm sure that I could be a movie star\n[02:27.140] If I could get out of this place\"\n[02:31.132] Oh la la-la di-dee-da\n[02:36.255] La-la di-dee-da da-dum\n[02:43.634] Now Paul is a real estate novelist\n[02:47.855] Who never had time for a wife\n[02:51.680] And he's talkin' with Davy who's still in the Navy\n[02:55.736] And probably will be for life\n[03:09.558] And the waitress is practicing politics\n[03:13.612] As the businessmen slowly get stoned\n[03:17.621] Yes they're sharing a drink they call loneliness\n[03:21.789] But it's better than drinkin' alone\n[03:41.914] Sing us a song you're the piano man\n[03:45.866] Sing us a song tonight\n[03:49.425] Well we're all in the mood for a melody\n[03:53.416] And you've got us feeling alright\n[04:11.715] It's a pretty good crowd for a Saturday\n[04:15.841] And the manager gives me a smile\n[04:19.658] 'Cause he knows that it's me they've been comin' to see\n[04:23.657] To forget about life for a while\n[04:29.274] And the piano it sounds like a carnival\n[04:33.337] And the microphone smells like a beer\n[04:37.186] And they sit at the bar and put bread in my jar\n[04:41.482] And say \"Man what are you doin' here\"\n[04:44.967] Oh la la-la di-dee-da\n[04:50.305] La-la di-dee-da da-dum\n[04:57.665] Sing us a song you're the piano man\n[05:01.625] Sing us a song tonight\n[05:04.942] Well we're all in the mood for a melody\n[05:09.169] And you've got us feeling alright",
