        "fullLyrics": "[00:34.000] Once upon a time\n[00:39.790] Not so long ago\n[00:44.620] Tommy used to work on the docks\n[00:48.550] Union's been on strike\n[00:50.320] He's down on his luck...it's tough' so tough\n[01:00.400] Gina works the diner all day\n[01:04.330] Working for her man' she brings home her pay\n[01:07.810] For love - for love\n[01:14.830] She says: We've got to hold on to what we've got\n[01:19.870] 'Cause it doesn't make a difference\n[01:21.760] If we make it or not\n[01:23.740] We've got each other and that's a lot\n[01:27.460] For love - we'll give it a shot\n[01:33.550] We're half way there\n[01:37.510] Livin' on a prayer\n[01:39.610] Take my hand and we'll make it - I swear\n[01:45.160] Livin' on a prayer\n[01:51.220] Tommy got his six string in hock\n[01:54.760] Now he's holding in what he used\n[01:57.490] To make it talk - so tough' it's tough\n[02:06.910] Gina dreams of running away\n[02:10.360] When she cries in the night\n[02:12.220] Tommy whispers: Baby it's okay' someday\n[02:21.640] We've got to hold on to what we've got\n[02:26.140] 'Cause it doesn't make a difference\n[02:28.030] If we make it or not\n[02:30.070] We've got each other and that's a lot\n[02:33.790] For love - we'll give it a shot\n[02:39.970] We're half way there\n[02:43.840] Livin' on a prayer\n[02:45.910] Take my hand and we'll make it - I swear\n[02:51.490] Livin' on a prayer\n[03:14.320] We've got to hold on ready or not\n[03:18.700] You live for the fight when it's all that you've got\n[03:22.390] We're half way there\n[03:28.000] Livin' on a prayer\n[03:30.190] Take my hand and we'll make it - I swear\n[03:35.710] Livin' on a prayer\n[03:37.840] We're half way there\n[03:43.360] Livin' on a prayer\n[03:45.580] Take my hand and we'll make it - I swear\n[03:51.070] Livin' on a prayer\n[03:53.230] We're half way there\n[03:56.740] Livin' on a prayer\n[03:59.950] Take my hand and we'll make it - I swear\n[04:01.480] Livin' on a prayer",
