        "fullLyrics": "[00:49.324] I was walking around just a face in the crowd\n[00:52.924] Trying to keep myself out of the rain\n[00:56.861] Saw a vagabond king wear a styrofoam crown\n[01:00.525] Wondered if I might end up the same\n[01:04.379] There s a man out on the corner\n[01:08.349] Singing old songs about change\n[01:12.879] Everybody got their cross to bare these days\n[01:19.319] She came looking for some shelter\n[01:23.005] With a suitcase full of dreams\n[01:26.704] To a motel room on the boulevard\n[01:30.254] Guess she s trying to be james dean\n[01:34.513] She s seen all the disciples\n[01:37.913] And all the wanna be s\n[01:42.375] No one wants to be themselves these days\n[01:48.899] Still there s nothing to hold on to but these days\n[01:55.954] These days the stars seem out of reach\n[02:03.519] These days there ain t a ladder on these streets\n[02:10.763] These days are fast love don t\n[02:15.023] Last in this graceless age\n[02:18.278] There ain t nobody left but us these days\n[02:25.392] Jimmy shoes busted both his legs\n[02:29.483] Trying to learn to fly\n[02:32.912] From a second story window\n[02:36.242] He just jumped and closed his eyes\n[02:40.487] His momma said he was crazy\n[02:43.702] He said momma I ve got to try\n[02:47.897] Don t you know that all my heroes died\n[02:55.047] And I guess I d rather die than fade away\n[03:01.925] These days the stars seem out of reach\n[03:09.631] But these days there ain t a ladder on these streets\n[03:16.726] These days are fast\n[03:19.291] Love don t lastsin this graceless age\n[03:24.291] Even innocence has caught the morning train\n[03:31.142] And there ain t nobody left but us these days\n[03:47.221] I know rome s still burning\n[03:50.696] Though the times have changed\n[03:54.446] This world keepd turning round and round and round and round\n[04:00.301] These days\n[04:28.382] These days the stars seem out of reach\n[04:35.976] But these days there ain t a ladder on the streets\n[04:42.983] These days are fast\n[04:45.406] Love don t lastsin this graceless age\n[04:50.360] Even innocence has caught the morning train\n[04:57.255] These days the stars seem out of reach\n[05:04.719] These days there ain t a ladder on the streets\n[05:11.797] These days are fast nothing lasts\n[05:15.569] There ain t no time to waste\n[05:18.912] There ain t nobody left to take the blame\n[05:27.074] There ain t nobody left but us these days\n[05:28.504] There ain t nobody left but us these days",
