        "fullLyrics": "[00:05.195] I got my first real six-string\n[00:08.185] Bought it at the five-and-dime\n[00:11.625] Played it till my fingers bled\n[00:14.935] It was the summer of '69\n[00:18.615] Me and some guys from school\n[00:21.825] Had a band and we tried real hard\n[00:25.175] Jimmy quit and Jody got married\n[00:28.505] I shoulda known we'd never get far\n[00:32.785] Oh when I look back now\n[00:35.595] That summer\n[00:36.375] Seemed to last forever\n[00:39.275] And if I had the choice\n[00:42.694] Ya I'd always wanna be there\n[00:46.164] Those were the best days\n[00:48.034] Of my life\n[00:57.024] Ain't no use in complainin'\n[00:59.984] When you got a job to do\n[01:03.004] Spent my evenin's\n[01:04.324] Down at the drive in\n[01:07.314] And that's when I met you\n[01:10.273] Standin' on your mama's porch\n[01:13.523] You told me\n[01:14.443] That you'd wait forever\n[01:17.253] Oh and when you held my hand\n[01:20.413] I knew that it was now or never\n[01:24.133] Those were the best days of my life\n[01:32.383] Back in the summer of '69\n[01:41.363] Man we were killin' time\n[01:43.593] We were young and restless\n[01:45.733] We needed to unwind\n[01:48.703] I guess nothin' can last forever\n[01:52.093] Forever no\n[02:09.005] And now the times are changin'\n[02:12.205] Look at everything\n[02:13.265] That's come and gone\n[02:15.625] Sometimes\n[02:16.345] When I play that old six-string\n[02:19.065] I think about ya wonder\n[02:20.225] What went wrong\n[02:22.795] Standin' on your mama's porch\n[02:26.005] You told me it would last forever\n[02:29.735] Oh the way you held my hand\n[02:32.825] I knew that it was now or never\n[02:36.595] Those were the best days of my life\n[02:44.884] Back in the summer of '69\n[02:51.794] It was the summer of '69\n[02:58.444] Baby baby '69\n[03:09.984] It was 7 7 7\n[03:13.792] '69",
