        "fullLyrics": "[00:33.802] Nobody on the road \n[00:36.831] Nobody on the beach \n[00:39.189] I feel it in the air \n[00:42.186] The summer's out of reach \n[00:44.066] Empty lake  empty streets \n[00:46.526] The sun goes down alone \n[00:50.336] I'm driving by your house\n[00:52.475] Though I know you're not home \n[00:55.183] But I can see you \n[00:57.942] Your brown skin shining in the sun \n[01:01.111] You got your hair combed back\n[01:03.291] Sunglasses on  baby \n[01:06.250] I can tell you my love for you will still be strong\n[01:11.167] After the boys of summer have gone \n[01:38.715] I never will forget those nights \n[01:41.422] I wonder if it was a dream \n[01:44.131] Remember how you made me crazy \n[01:46.801] Remember how I made you scream \n[01:49.441] Now I don't understand what\n[01:51.620] Happened to our love \n[01:54.530] But  baby  I'm gonna get you back \n[01:57.167] I'm gonna show you what I'm made of \n[02:00.374] I can see you \n[02:02.933] Your brown skin shining in the sun \n[02:06.051] I see you walking real slow and you're\n[02:08.050] Smiling at everyone \n[02:11.578] I can tell you my love\n[02:13.537] For you will still be strong\n[02:15.867] After the boys of summer have gone \n[03:05.730] Out on the road today I saw a DEADHEAD\n[03:08.036] Sticker on a Cadillac \n[03:10.435] A little voice inside my head said:\n[03:12.743] \"Don't look back  you can never look back \"\n[03:16.011] I thought I knew what love was \n[03:18.419] What did I know\n[03:21.338] Those days are gone forever \n[03:24.035] I should just let them go  but\n[03:27.065] I can see you \n[03:29.464] Your brown skin shining in the sun \n[03:32.693] You got that top pulled down \n[03:34.513] Radio on  baby \n[03:37.902] I can tell you my love\n[03:40.210] For you will still be strong \n[03:42.579] After the boys of summer have gone \n[03:48.777] I can see you \n[03:51.236] Your brown skin shining in the sun \n[03:54.394] You got that hair slicked back \n[03:55.784] And those Wayfarers on  baby \n[03:59.632] I can tell you my love\n[04:01.821] For you will still be strong \n[04:04.171] After the boys of summer have gone",
