        "fullLyrics": "[00:28.972] Came in from a rainy Thursday on the avenue\n[00:35.732] Thought I heard you talking softly\n[00:42.636] I turned on the lights the TV and the radio\n[00:49.460] Still I can't escape the ghost of you\n[00:56.437] What has happened to it all\n[00:59.686] Crazy some'd say\n[01:03.111] Where is the life that I recognize\n[01:09.189] Gone away\n[01:10.638] But I won't cry for yesterday\n[01:14.324] There's an ordinary world\n[01:17.772] Somehow I have to find\n[01:24.533] And as I try to make my way\n[01:28.261] To the ordinary world\n[01:31.454] I will learn to survive\n[01:44.518] Passion or coincidence once prompted you to say\n[01:51.179] Pride will tear us both apart\n[01:56.732] Well now pride's gone out the window\n[02:00.701] 'Cross the rooftops run away\n[02:04.796] Left me in the vacuum of my heart\n[02:11.699] What is happening to me\n[02:15.128] Crazy some'd say\n[02:18.607] Where is my friend when I need you most\n[02:24.505] Gone away\n[02:26.234] But I won't cry for yesterday\n[02:29.727] There's an ordinary world\n[02:33.169] Somehow I have to find\n[02:39.728] And as I try to make my way\n[02:43.551] To the ordinary world\n[02:46.893] I will learn to survive\n[02:55.610] Ooh ah\n[03:06.727] Hey hey oh\n[03:20.444] Papers in the roadside tell of suffering and greed\n[03:27.179] Fear today forgot tomorrow\n[03:32.744] Ooh here beside the news of holy war and holy need\n[03:40.832] Ours is just a little sorrowed talk\n[03:59.983] Just blown away\n[04:15.629] And I don't cry for yesterday\n[04:19.526] There's an ordinary world\n[04:22.782] Somehow I have to find\n[04:29.587] And as I try to make my way\n[04:33.147] To the ordinary world\n[04:36.505] I will learn to survive\n[04:41.732] Every world\n[04:48.490] Is my world\n[04:50.145] I will learn to survive\n[04:55.474] Any world\n[05:02.194] Is my world\n[05:03.872] I will learn to survive\n[05:09.077] Any world\n[05:15.897] Is my world\n[05:22.720] Every world\n[05:29.589] Is my world",
