        "externalUrl": "",
        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:19.778] Desperado why don't you come to your senses\n[00:28.512] You've been out ridin' fences\n[00:32.998] For so long now\n[00:36.662] Oh you're a hard one\n[00:39.836] I know that you got your reasons\n[00:44.768] These things that are pleasin' you\n[00:49.223] Can hurt you somehow\n[00:54.901] Don't you draw the queen of diamonds boy\n[00:58.835] She'll beat you if she's able\n[01:02.831] You know the queen of hearts is always your best bet\n[01:10.427] Now it seems to me some fine things\n[01:14.341] Have been laid upon your table\n[01:17.977] But you only want the ones\n[01:21.305] That you can't get\n[01:24.625] Desperado\n[01:29.285] Oh you ain't getting no younger\n[01:34.397] Your pain and your hunger\n[01:38.209] They're driving you home\n[01:42.460] And freedom oh freedom\n[01:45.928] Well that's just some people talking\n[01:49.877] Your prison is walking through this world all alone\n[01:59.864] Don't your feet get cold in the winter time\n[02:03.944] The sky won't snow and the sun won't shine\n[02:07.718] It's hard to tell the night time from the day\n[02:15.246] And you're losing all your highs and lows\n[02:19.360] Ain't it funny how the feeling goes\n[02:23.654] Away\n[02:29.632] Desperado\n[02:34.330] Why don't you come to your senses\n[02:39.031] Come down from your fences open the gate\n[02:47.008] It may be rainin' but there's a rainbow above you\n[02:54.922] You better let somebody love you\n[02:59.893] Let somebody love you\n[03:02.316] You better let somebody love you\n[03:08.654] Before it's too late",
