        "fullLyrics": "[00:20.847] I can't light no more of your darkness\n[00:34.518] All my pictures seem to fade to black and white\n[00:48.655] I'm growing tired and time stands still before me\n[01:02.924] Frozen here on the ladder of my life\n[01:16.867] It's much too late to save myself from falling\n[01:30.950] I took a chance and changed your way of life\n[01:45.031] But you misread my meaning when I met you\n[01:59.405] Closed the door and left me blinded by the light\n[02:13.231] Don't let the sun go down on me\n[02:19.929] Although I search myself it's always someone else I see\n[02:26.884] I'd just allow a fragment of your life to wander free\n[02:40.129] But losing everything is like the sun going down on me\n[03:02.352] I can't find\n[03:06.666] Oh the right romantic line\n[03:16.067] But see me once see the way I feel\n[03:29.941] Don't discard me baby don't\n[03:34.211] Just because you think I mean you harm\n[03:37.306] Just because you think I mean you harm oh\n[03:43.096] But these cuts I have cuts I have\n[03:48.658] They need love\n[03:49.836] They need love they need love to help them heal\n[03:54.751] Oh don't let the sun go down on me\n[04:03.543] Although I search myself it's always someone else I see\n[04:10.507] I'd just allow a fragment of your life to wander free\n[04:23.670] 'Cause losing everything is like the sun going down on me\n[04:45.555] Don't let the sun go down on me\n[04:51.920] Although I search myself it's always someone else I that see yeah\n[04:59.264] I'd just allow a fragment of your life to wander free baby oh\n[05:12.529] 'Cause losing everything is like the sun going down on me",
