        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:59.872] Winding your way down on Baker Street\n[01:04.120] Light in your head and dead on your feet\n[01:06.930] Well  another crazy day\n[01:09.900] You'll drink the night away\n[01:11.380] And forget about everything\n[01:16.580] This city desert makes you feel so cold\n[01:19.900] It's got so many people  but it's got no soul\n[01:23.970] And it's taken you so long\n[01:26.660] To find out you were wrong\n[01:28.400] When you thought it held everything\n[01:33.330] You used to think that it was so easy\n[01:37.500] You used to say that it was so easy\n[01:41.110] But you're trying  you're trying now\n[01:50.020] Another year and then you'd be happy\n[01:53.380] Just one more year and then you'd be happy\n[01:57.880] But you're crying  you're crying now\n[02:41.013] Way down the street there's a light in his place\n[02:44.833] He opens the door  he's got that look on his face\n[02:48.803] And he asks you where you've been\n[02:51.053] You tell him who you've seen\n[02:53.063] And you talk about anything\n[02:57.193] He's got this dream about buying some land\n[03:00.813] He's gonna give up the booze and the one-night stands\n[03:05.533] And then he'll settle down\n[03:07.723] In some quiet little town\n[03:09.763] And forget about everything\n[03:14.643] But you know he'll always keep moving\n[03:18.693] You know he's never gonna stop moving\n[03:22.453] 'Cause he's rolling  he's the rolling stone\n[03:31.493] And when you wake up  it's a new morning\n[03:35.523] The sun is shining  it's a new morning\n[03:39.243] And you're going  you're going home",
