        "fullLyrics": "[00:18.400] Just a small town girl\n[00:21.890] Livin' in a lonely world\n[00:26.260] She took the midnight train goin' anywhere\n[00:34.490] Just a city boy\n[00:38.240] Born and raised in south Detroit\n[00:42.540] He took the midnight train goin' anywhere\n[01:06.570] A singer in a smoky room\n[01:10.500] A smell of wine and cheap perfume\n[01:14.310] For a smile they can share the night\n[01:17.180] It goes on and on and on and on\n[01:21.860] Strangers waiting\n[01:26.910] Up and down the boulevard\n[01:29.600] Their shadows searching in the night\n[01:37.900] Streetlights people\n[01:42.940] Living just to find emotion\n[01:46.060] Hiding somewhere in the night\n[02:03.040] Working hard to get my fill\n[02:06.910] Everybody wants a thrill\n[02:10.400] Payin' anything to roll the dice just one more time\n[02:18.140] Some will win  some will lose\n[02:22.510] Some were born to sing the blues\n[02:26.080] Oh  the movie never ends\n[02:28.890] It goes on and on and on and on\n[02:33.570] Strangers waiting\n[02:38.590] Up and down the boulevard\n[02:41.150] Their shadows searching in the night\n[02:49.780] Streetlight people\n[02:54.650] Living just to find emotion\n[02:57.590] Hiding somewhere in the night\n[03:21.580] Don't stop believin'\n[03:25.090] Hold on to that feelin'\n[03:29.320] Streetlight people\n[03:37.450] Don't stop believin'\n[03:41.070] Hold on\n[03:45.070] Streetlight people\n[03:53.270] Don't stop believin'\n[03:57.520] Hold on to that feelin'\n[04:01.140] Streetlight people",
