        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:13.490] I thought I saw a man brought to life\n[00:18.500] He was warm, he came around like he was dignified\n[00:24.000] He showed me what it was to cry\n[00:28.010] Well you couldn't be that man I adored\n[00:33.050] You don't seem to know, don't seem to care what your heart is for\n[00:38.900] But I don't know him anymore\n[00:41.480] There's nothing where he used to lie\n[00:44.270] My conversation has run dry\n[00:47.450] That's whats going on, nothing's fine I'm torn\n[00:52.700] I'm all out of faith, this is how I feel\n[00:57.740] I'm cold and I am shamed lying naked on the floor\n[01:02.480] Illusion never changed into something real\n[01:07.670] I'm wide awake and I can see the perfect sky is torn\n[01:12.530] You're a little late, I'm already torn\n[01:23.210] So I guess the fortune teller's right\n[01:28.310] Should have seen just what was there and not some holy light\n[01:33.650] To crawl beneath my veins and now\n[01:36.440] I don't care, I have no luck, I don't miss it all that much\n[01:42.200] There's just so many things that I can't touch, I'm torn\n[01:47.510] I'm all out of faith, this is how I feel\n[01:52.550] I'm cold and I am shamed lying naked on the floor\n[01:57.320] Illusion never changed into something real\n[02:02.510] I'm wide awake and I can see the perfect sky is torn\n[02:07.430] You're a little late, I'm already torn. Torn.\n[02:31.100] There's nothing where he used to lie\n[02:33.890] My inspiration has run dry\n[02:37.100] That's what's going on, nothings right, I'm torn\n[02:42.410] I'm all out of faith, this is how I feel\n[02:47.390] I'm cold and I am shamed lying naked on the floor\n[02:52.220] Illusion never changed into something real\n[02:57.320] I'm wide awake and I can see the perfect sky is torn\n[03:02.300] I'm all out of faith, this is how I feel\n[03:07.340] I'm cold and I'm ashamed bound and broken on the floor\n[03:12.230] You're a little late, I'm already torn",
