        "fullLyrics": "[00:46.340] Lost in the high street, where the dogs run\n[00:50.390] Roaming suburban boys\n[00:54.140] Mother's got her hairdo to be done\n[00:57.830] She says they're too old for toys\n[01:01.850] Stood by the bus stop with a felt pen\n[01:06.020] in this suburban hell\n[01:09.650] and in the distance a police car\n[01:13.430] to break the suburban spell\n[01:19.370] Let's take a ride\n[01:22.250] and run with the dogs tonight\n[01:25.250] in suburbia\n[01:28.430] You can't hide\n[01:30.110] Run with the dogs tonight\n[01:33.020] in suburbia\n[01:35.270] Break the window by the town hall\n[01:38.780] Listen! A siren screams\n[01:42.500] there in the distance like a roll call\n[01:46.580] of all the suburban dreams\n[01:52.340] Let's take a ride\n[01:55.160] and run with the dogs tonight\n[01:58.160] in suburbia\n[02:01.310] You can't hide\n[02:03.020] run with the dogs tonight\n[02:05.930] in suburbia\n[02:23.840] I only wanted something else to do but hang around\n[02:31.580] I only wanted something else to do but hang around\n[02:39.350] I only wanted something else to do but hang around\n[02:47.150] I only wanted something else to do but hang around\n[03:13.580] It's on the front page of the papers\n[03:17.540] This is their hour of need\n[03:21.230] Where's a policeman when you need one\n[03:25.070] to blame the colour TV?\n[03:31.070] Let's take a ride\n[03:33.950] and run with the dogs tonight\n[03:36.920] in suburbia\n[03:40.070] You can't hide\n[03:41.780] run with the dogs tonight\n[03:44.660] in suburbia\n[03:47.570] Let's take a ride\n[03:49.250] and run with the dogs tonight\n[03:52.400] in suburbia\n[03:55.610] You can't hide\n[03:57.560] run with the dogs tonight\n[04:00.170] in suburbia\n[04:04.730] run with the dogs tonight\n[04:08.000] in suburbia\n[04:11.090] You can't hide\n[04:31.130] in suburbia",
