        "fullLyrics": "[00:20.270] Empty spaces - what are we living for\n[00:25.850] Abandoned places - I guess we know the score\n[00:32.420] On and on\n[00:35.090] Does anybody know what we are looking for\n[00:40.130] Another hero another mindless crime\n[00:45.950] Behind the curtain in the pantomime\n[00:52.370] Hold the line\n[00:55.100] Does anybody want to take it anymore\n[00:59.690] The show must go on\n[01:05.420] The show must go on\n[01:11.900] Inside my heart is breaking\n[01:15.080] My make-up may be flaking\n[01:17.390] But my smile still stays on\n[01:25.850] Whatever happens I'll leave it all to chance\n[01:31.550] Another heartache another failed romance\n[01:38.090] On and on\n[01:40.730] Does anybody know what we are living for\n[01:45.800] I guess I'm learning\n[01:48.500] I must be warmer now\n[01:51.350] I'll soon be turning round the corner now\n[01:57.590] Outside the dawn is breaking\n[02:00.770] But inside in the dark I'm aching to be free\n[02:07.940] The show must go on\n[02:14.000] The show must go on - yeah\n[02:19.970] Ooh inside my heart is breaking\n[02:23.630] My make-up may be flaking\n[02:25.940] But my smile still stays on\n[02:35.510] Yeah oh oh oh\n[02:49.790] My soul is painted like the wings of butterflies\n[02:55.100] Fairy tales of yesterday will grow but never die\n[03:00.800] I can fly - my friends\n[03:05.450] The show must go on - yeah\n[03:11.180] The show must go on\n[03:17.600] I'll face it with a grin\n[03:20.480] I'm never giving in\n[03:22.880] On with the show\n[03:37.790] I'll top the bill\n[03:39.200] I'll overkill\n[03:40.850] I have to find the will to carry on\n[03:45.140] On with the\n[03:46.370] On with the show\n[03:49.400] The show must go on\n[04:01.130] Producers : David Richards / Queen\n[04:01.910] Lead Vocals : Freddie Mercury\n[04:02.690] Electric Guitar : Brian May\n[04:03.320] Bass Guitar : John Deacon\n[04:05.600] Keyboards & Programming : Brian May\n[04:07.760] Drum Kit : Roger Taylor\n[04:08.810] Backing Vocals : Brian May / Roger Taylor\n[04:11.900] Recorded in 1990",
