        "externalUrl": "",
        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:31.430] My mother came to hazard when I was just seven\n[00:35.800] Even then the folks in town said with prejudiced eyes\n[00:42.540] That boy＇s not right\n[00:46.780] Three years ago when I came to know Mary\n[00:51.040] First time that someone looked beyond the rumors and the lies\n[00:57.910] And saw the man inside\n[01:01.900] We used to walk down by the river\n[01:09.390] She loved to watch the sun go down\n[01:17.310] We used to walk along the river\n[01:24.920] And dream our way out of this town\n[01:48.450] No one understood what I felt for Mary\n[01:52.760] No one cared until the night she went out walking alone\n[01:59.180] And never came home\n[02:03.680] Man with a badge came knocking next morning\n[02:08.040] Here was I surrounded by a thousand fingers suddenly\n[02:14.600] Pointed right at me\n[02:18.650] I swear I left her by the river\n[02:26.390] I swear I left her safe and sound\n[02:34.000] I need to make it to the river\n[02:41.990] And leave this old Nebraska town\n[02:50.540] I think about my life gone by\n[02:53.720] And how it＇s done me wrong\n[02:57.840] There＇s no escape for me this time\n[03:01.460] All of my rescues are gone  long gone\n[03:37.640] I swear I left her by the river\n[03:45.190] I swear I left her safe and sound\n[03:52.510] I need to make it to the river\n[04:00.620] And leave this old Nebraska town",
