        "fullLyrics": "[00:03.360] Hello darkness my old friend\n[00:07.860] l’ve come to talk with you again\n[00:12.330] Because a vision softly creeping\n[00:17.070] left its seeds while I was sleeping\n[00:21.690] And the vision\n[00:23.910] that was planted in my brain\n[00:28.200] Still remains\n[00:31.500] within the sound of silence\n[00:37.320] In restless dreams I walked alone\n[00:42.180] narrow streets of cobblestone\n[00:46.650] Neath the halo of a street lamp\n[00:50.940] I turned my collar to the cold and damp\n[00:55.770] When my eyes were stabbed by the flash of a neon light\n[01:02.370] That split the night and touched the sound of silence\n[01:11.550] And in the naked light I saw\n[01:15.990] ten thousand people maybe more\n[01:20.730] People talking without speaking\n[01:24.870] people hearing without listening\n[01:29.640] People writing songs\n[01:33.060] that voices never share\n[01:37.230] No one dare disturb the sound of silence\n[01:46.380] Fools said I you do not know silence like a cancer grows\n[01:55.200] Hear my words that I might teach you\n[01:59.520] take my arms that I might reach you\n[02:03.990] But my words like silent raindrops fell\n[02:13.170] And echoed in the wells of silence\n[02:20.670] And the people bowed and prayed to the neon god they made\n[02:29.370] And the sign flashed out its warning\n[02:33.780] in the words that it was forming\n[02:38.130] And the sign said the words of the prophets are written on the subway walls\n[02:45.600] And tenement halls\n[02:48.630] and whispered in the sounds of silence",
