        "fullLyrics": "[00:20.501] I walked through the door with you\n[00:23.636] The air was cold\n[00:25.833] But something 'bout it felt like home somehow and I\n[00:31.412] Left my scarf there at your sister's house\n[00:35.226] And you've still got it\n[00:38.284] In your drawer even now\n[00:51.166] Oh your sweet disposition\n[00:53.897] And my wide eyed gaze\n[00:56.942] We're singing in the car getting lost upstate\n[01:02.183] Autumn leaves falling down like pieces into place\n[01:06.134] And I can picture it after all these days\n[01:12.063] And I know it's long gone and\n[01:14.678] That magic's not here no more\n[01:17.255] And I might be okay but I'm not fine at all\n[01:22.565] Oh oh oh\n[01:27.787] 'Cause there we are again on that little town street\n[01:32.793] You almost ran the red 'cause you were looking over at me\n[01:37.374] Wind in my hair I was there I remember it all too well\n[01:47.899] Photo album on the counter\n[01:51.003] Your cheeks were turning red\n[01:52.930] You used to be a little kid with glasses in a twin sized bed\n[01:58.548] And your mother's telling stories 'bout you on the tee ball team\n[02:03.915] You tell me about your past thinking your future was me\n[02:08.393] And I know it's long gone and\n[02:11.562] There was nothing else I could do\n[02:13.966] And I forget about you long enough\n[02:16.577] To forget why I needed to\n[02:24.449] 'Cause there we are again in the middle of the night\n[02:29.701] We're dancing round the kitchen in the refrigerator light\n[02:34.008] Down the stairs I was there I remember it all too well yeah\n[02:59.849] Maybe we got lost in translation\n[03:02.801] Maybe I asked for too much\n[03:05.023] But maybe this thing was a masterpiece\n[03:08.201] 'til you tore it all up\n[03:10.265] Running scared I was there I remember it all too well\n[03:20.579] And you call me up again just to break me like a promise\n[03:26.312] So casually cruel in the name of being honest\n[03:30.827] I'm a crumpled up piece of paper lying here\n[03:35.153] 'Cause I remember it all all all\n[03:43.792] Too well\n[03:55.017] Time won't fly it's like I'm paralyzed by it\n[03:59.830] I'd like to be my old self again\n[04:02.540] But I'm still trying to find it\n[04:04.816] After plaid shirt days and nights when you made me your own\n[04:10.233] Now you mail back my things and I walk home alone\n[04:15.323] But you keep my old scarf\n[04:17.603] From that very first week\n[04:20.410] 'Cause it reminds you of innocence\n[04:23.074] And it smells like me\n[04:25.154] You can't get rid of it\n[04:27.826] 'Cause you remember it all too well yeah\n[04:36.075] 'Cause there we are again when I loved you so\n[04:41.452] Back before you lost the one real thing you've ever known\n[04:45.825] It was rare I was there I remember it all too well\n[04:56.004] Wind in my hair you were there you remember it all\n[05:01.128] Down the stairs you were there you remember it all\n[05:06.424] It was rare I was there I remember it all too well",
