        "fullLyrics": "[00:05.499] I have this thing where I get older but just never wiser\n[00:10.458] Midnights become my afternoons\n[00:15.386] When my depression works the graveyard shift\n[00:18.430] All of the people I've ghosted stand there in the room\n[00:24.692] I should not be left to my own devices\n[00:28.095] They come with prices and vices\n[00:30.505] I end up in crisis\n[00:32.605] Tale as old as time\n[00:35.188] I wake up screaming from dreaming\n[00:37.581] One day I'll watch as you're leaving\n[00:40.109] Cause you got tired of my scheming\n[00:42.568] For the last time\n[00:44.484] It's me hi I'm the problem it's me\n[00:49.432] At teatime everybody agrees\n[00:54.984] I'll stare directly at the sun but never in the mirror\n[00:59.874] It must be exhausting always rooting for the anti-hero\n[01:09.805] Sometimes I feel like everybody is a sexy baby\n[01:14.842] And I'm a monster on the hill\n[01:19.751] Too big to hang out slowly lurching toward your favorite city\n[01:24.696] Pierced through the heart but never killed\n[01:29.628] Did you hear my covert narcissism I disguise as altruism\n[01:35.046] Like some kind of congressman\n[01:37.218] Tale as old as time\n[01:39.553] I wake up screaming from dreaming\n[01:42.003] One day I'll watch as you're leaving\n[01:44.567] And life will lose all its meaning\n[01:46.876] For the last time\n[01:48.804] It's me hi I'm the problem it's me\n[01:53.775] At teatime everybody agrees\n[01:59.319] I'll stare directly at the sun but never in the mirror\n[02:04.201] It must be exhausting always rooting for the anti-hero\n[02:14.191] I have this dream my daughter-in-law kills me for the money\n[02:19.071] She thinks I left them in the will\n[02:24.111] The family gathers around and reads it and then someone screams out\n[02:28.925] \"She's laughing up at us from hell\"\n[02:33.385] It's me hi I'm the problem it's me\n[02:38.474] It's me hi I'm the problem it's me\n[02:43.405] It's me hi everybody agrees\n[02:48.144] Everybody agrees\n[02:53.243] It's me hi I'm the problem it's me (I'm the problem it's me)\n[02:58.164] At teatime everybody agrees\n[03:02.082] Everybody agrees\n[03:03.672] I'll stare directly at the sun but never in the mirror\n[03:08.545] It must be exhausting always rooting for the anti-hero",
