        "fullLyrics": "[00:14.758] I'm so glad you made time to see me\n[00:18.288] How's life tell me how's your family\n[00:21.544] I haven't seen them in a while\n[00:28.214] You've been good busier than ever\n[00:31.575] We small talk work and the weather\n[00:35.029] Your guard is up and I know why\n[00:41.759] Because the last time you saw me\n[00:44.492] Is still burned in the back of your mind\n[00:47.684] You gave me roses and I left them there to die\n[00:54.888] So this is me swallowing my pride\n[00:57.649] Standing in front of you saying I'm sorry for that night\n[01:04.081] And I go back to December all the time\n[01:08.359] It turns out freedom ain't nothing but missing you\n[01:11.989] Wishing I'd realized what I had when you were mine\n[01:17.587] I'd go back to December turn around and make it all right\n[01:24.458] I go back to December all the time\n[01:42.854] These days I haven't been sleeping\n[01:45.698] Staying up playing back myself leavin'\n[01:49.324] When your birthday passed and I didn't call\n[01:55.518] And I think about summer all the beautiful times\n[01:59.154] I watched you laughing from the passenger side\n[02:02.929] Realized I loved you in the fall\n[02:09.735] And then the cold came the dark days when fear crept into my mind\n[02:15.555] You gave me all your love and all I gave you was goodbye\n[02:22.736] So this is me swallowing my pride\n[02:25.552] Standing in front of you saying I'm sorry for that night\n[02:31.983] And I go back to December all the time\n[02:36.273] It turns out freedom ain't nothing but missing you\n[02:39.891] Wishing I'd realized what I had when you were mine\n[02:45.570] I'd go back to December turn around and change my own mind\n[02:52.314] I go back to December all the time\n[03:09.087] I miss your tanned skin your sweet smile\n[03:13.294] So good to me so right\n[03:16.048] And how you held me in your arms that September night\n[03:20.858] The first time you ever saw me cry\n[03:24.549] Maybe this is wishful thinking\n[03:27.939] Probably mindless dreaming\n[03:30.784] But if we loved again I swear I'd love you right\n[03:36.848] I'd go back in time and change it but I can't\n[03:43.499] So if the chain is on your door I understand\n[03:50.751] But this is me swallowing my pride\n[03:53.422] Standing in front of you saying I'm sorry for that night\n[03:59.698] And I go back to December\n[04:04.278] It turns out freedom ain't nothing but missing you\n[04:07.795] Wishing I'd realized what I had when you were mine\n[04:13.307] I'd go back to December turn around and make it all right\n[04:20.253] I'd go back to December turn around and change my own mind\n[04:27.066] I go back to December all the time\n[04:37.370] All the time",
