        "fullLyrics": "[00:12.090] I was riding shot-gun\n[00:13.320] With my hair undone\n[00:14.619] In the front seat of his car\n[00:17.279] He's got a one-hand feel\n[00:18.649] On the steering wheel\n[00:20.269] The other on my heart\n[00:23.248] I look around turn the radio down\n[00:25.428] He says baby is something wrong\n[00:28.268] I say nothing I was just thinking\n[00:30.767] How we don't have a song\n[00:34.417] And he says\n[00:35.617] Our song is a slamming\n[00:36.947] Screen door\n[00:38.107] Sneakin' out late tapping\n[00:39.277] On your window\n[00:40.987] When we're on the phone\n[00:42.367] And you talk real slow\n[00:44.336] Cause it's late and your mama\n[00:45.665] Don't know\n[00:46.254] Our song is the way you laugh\n[00:48.564] The first date man I didn't kiss her\n[00:50.444] And I should have\n[00:52.004] And when I got home before\n[00:55.222] I said amen\n[00:57.532] Asking God if he could play it again\n[01:07.991] I was walking up the front porch steps\n[01:09.971] After everything that day\n[01:12.851] Had gone all wrong\n[01:13.971] Or been trampled on\n[01:15.241] And lost and thrown away\n[01:18.360] Got to the hallway well on my way\n[01:21.099] To my lovin' bed\n[01:23.478] I almost didn't notice all the roses\n[01:26.406] And the note that said\n[01:29.396] Our song is a slamming screen door\n[01:31.776] Sneakin' out late tapping\n[01:33.105] On your window\n[01:34.905] When we're on the phone\n[01:36.255] And you talk real slow\n[01:38.355] Cause it's late\n[01:39.005] And your mama don't know\n[01:40.245] Our song is the way you laugh\n[01:42.335] The first date man\n[01:43.645] I didn't kiss her and I should have\n[01:45.855] And when I got home before\n[01:49.135] I said amen\n[01:51.455] Asking God if he could play it again\n[02:08.051] I've heard every album listened\n[02:10.871] To the radio\n[02:13.321] Waited for something to come along\n[02:18.600] That was as good as our song\n[02:22.010] Cause our song is a slamming\n[02:23.369] Screen door\n[02:24.208] Sneaking out late tapping\n[02:25.746] On his window\n[02:27.396] When we're on the phone\n[02:28.896] And he talks real slow\n[02:30.796] Cause it's late and his mama\n[02:32.055] Don't know\n[02:33.025] Our song is the way he laughs\n[02:34.824] The first date man I didn't kiss him\n[02:37.093] And I should have\n[02:38.303] And when I got home before\n[02:41.731] I said amen\n[02:44.020] Asking God if he could play it again\n[02:53.090] Play it again\n[03:04.669] I was riding shot-gun\n[03:05.679] With my hair undone\n[03:07.199] In the front seat of his car\n[03:10.529] I grabbed a pen and an old napkin\n[03:12.619] And I wrote down our song",
