        "fullLyrics": "[00:12.871] Elevator buttons and morning air\n[00:18.757] Strangers' silence makes me want to take the stairs\n[00:24.584] If you were here we'd laugh about their vacant stares\n[00:29.955] But right now my time is theirs\n[00:36.371] Seems like there's always someone who disapproves\n[00:42.529] They'll judge it like they know about me and you\n[00:48.383] And the verdict comes from those with nothing else to do\n[00:53.975] The jury's out but my choice is you\n[01:00.660] So don't you worry your pretty little mind\n[01:03.808] People throw rocks at things that shine\n[01:06.406] And life makes love look hard\n[01:11.942] The stakes are high the water's rough\n[01:17.471] But this love is ours\n[01:30.727] You never know what people have up their sleeves\n[01:36.983] Ghosts from your past gonna jump out at me\n[01:42.801] Lurking in the shadows with their lip gloss smiles\n[01:47.673] But I don't care 'cause right now you're mine\n[01:53.770] And you'll say\n[01:54.815] Don't you worry your pretty little mind\n[01:57.883] People throw rocks at things that shine\n[02:00.433] And life makes love look hard\n[02:05.977] The stakes are high the water's rough\n[02:11.601] But this love is ours\n[02:25.535] And it's not theirs to speculate if it's wrong\n[02:30.185] And your hands are tough but they are where mine belong\n[02:36.113] And I'll fight their doubt and give you faith\n[02:40.647] With this song for you\n[02:49.128] 'Cause I love the gap between your teeth\n[02:55.117] And I love the riddles that you speak\n[03:00.013] And any snide remarks from my father about your tattoos will be ignored\n[03:08.690] 'Cause my heart is yours\n[03:12.725] So don't you worry your pretty little mind\n[03:15.863] People throw rocks at things that shine\n[03:18.501] And life makes love look hard\n[03:24.831] Don't you worry your pretty little mind\n[03:27.855] People throw rocks at things that shine\n[03:30.417] But they can't take what's ours\n[03:36.960] They can't take what's ours\n[03:42.072] The stakes are high the water's rough\n[03:47.708] But this love is ours",
