        "fullLyrics": "[00:06.621] Loving him is like driving a new Maserati\n[00:10.120] Down a dead-end street\n[00:15.644] Faster than the wind passionate as sin\n[00:18.603] Ending so suddenly\n[00:21.935] Loving him is like trying to change your mind\n[00:24.833] Once you're already flying through the free fall\n[00:30.637] Like the colors in autumn so bright\n[00:33.436] Just before they lose it all\n[00:37.809] Losing him was blue like I'd never known\n[00:41.685] Missing him was dark grey all alone\n[00:45.288] Forgetting him was like\n[00:46.851] Trying to know somebody you never met\n[00:52.958] But loving him was red\n[01:00.731] Loving him was red\n[01:08.087] Touching him was like realizing all you ever wanted\n[01:11.771] Was right there in front of you\n[01:15.341] Memorizing him was as easy as knowing\n[01:18.356] All the words to your old favorite song\n[01:23.135] Fighting with him was like trying to solve a crossword\n[01:26.141] And realizing there's no right answer\n[01:30.853] Regretting him was like wishing you never found out\n[01:34.702] That love could be that strong\n[01:39.268] Losing him was blue like I'd never known\n[01:43.070] Missing him was dark grey all alone\n[01:46.686] Forgetting him was like\n[01:48.303] Trying to know somebody you never met\n[01:54.406] But loving him was red\n[01:58.241] Oh red\n[02:02.327] Burning red\n[02:08.764] Remembering him comes in flashbacks and echoes\n[02:13.831] Tell myself it's time now gotta let go\n[02:17.384] But moving on from him is impossible\n[02:20.377] When I still see it all in my head\n[02:25.080] In burning red\n[02:32.942] Loving him was red\n[02:40.015] Oh losing him was blue like I'd never known\n[02:44.506] Missing him was dark grey all alone\n[02:48.114] Forgetting him was like\n[02:49.796] Trying to know somebody you never met\n[02:55.800] 'Cause loving him was red\n[02:58.319] Yeah yeah red\n[03:03.493] We're burning red\n[03:11.654] And that's why he's spinning 'round in my head\n[03:16.285] Comes back to me burning red\n[03:21.593] Yeah yeah\n[03:26.669] His love was like driving a new Maserati\n[03:29.908] Down a dead-end street",
