        "fullLyrics": "[00:11.019] Drew looks at me\n[00:15.775] I fake a smile so he won't see\n[00:20.375] That I want and I'm needing\n[00:26.354] Everything that we should be\n[00:29.296] I'll bet she's beautiful that girl he talks about\n[00:34.079] And she's got everything that I have to live without\n[00:39.838] Drew talks to me\n[00:44.629] I laugh 'cause it's just so funny\n[00:49.076] That I can't even see\n[00:55.068] Anyone when he's with me\n[00:58.116] He says he's so in love he's finally got it right\n[01:02.855] I wonder if he knows he's all I think about at night\n[01:07.998] He's the reason for the teardrops on my guitar\n[01:12.493] The only thing that keeps me wishing on a wishing star\n[01:17.189] He's the song in the car\n[01:19.580] I keep singing don't know why I do\n[01:27.735] Drew walks by me\n[01:33.487] Can't he tell that I can't breathe\n[01:37.064] And there he goes so perfectly\n[01:42.528] The kind of flawless I wish I could be\n[01:46.095] She'd better hold him tight give him all her love\n[01:50.815] Look in those beautiful eyes and know she's lucky 'cause\n[01:55.943] He's the reason for the teardrops on my guitar\n[02:00.431] The only thing that keeps me wishing on a wishing star\n[02:05.216] He's the song in the car\n[02:07.690] I keep singing don't know why I do\n[02:24.440] So I drive home alone as I turn off the light\n[02:29.224] I'll put his picture down and maybe get some sleep tonight\n[02:34.280] He's the reason for the teardrops on my guitar\n[02:38.814] The only one who's got enough of me to break my heart\n[02:43.610] He's the song in the car\n[02:46.018] I keep singing don't know why I do\n[02:52.110] He's the time taken up but there's never enough\n[02:56.869] And he's all that I need to fall into\n[03:03.691] Drew looks at me\n[03:08.590] I fake a smile so he won't see",
