        "externalUrl": "",
        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:31.280] I hear the drums echoing tonight\n[00:34.880] But she hears only whispers of some quiet conversation\n[00:43.010] She's coming in 12:30 flight\n[00:46.550] The moonlit wings reflect the stars that guide me towards salvation\n[00:54.770] I stopped an old man along the way\n[00:58.340] Hoping to find some long forgotten words or ancient melodies\n[01:06.350] He turned to me as if to say' \"Hurry boy' it's waiting there for you\"\n[01:16.760] It's gonna take a lot to drag me away from you\n[01:21.770] There's nothing that a hundred men or more could ever do\n[01:27.110] I bless the rains down in Africa\n[01:32.330] Gonna take some time to do the things we never had\n[01:50.270] The wild dogs cry out in the night\n[01:53.690] As they grow restless longing for some solitary company\n[02:02.060] I know that I must do what's right\n[02:04.940] Sure as Kilimanjaro rises like Olympus above the Serengeti\n[02:13.700] I seek to cure what's deep inside' frightened of this thing that I've become\n[02:23.990] It's gonna take a lot to drag me away from you\n[02:29.270] There's nothing that a hundred men or more could ever do\n[02:34.460] I bless the rains down in Africa\n[02:39.710] Gonna take some time to do the things we never had\n[03:12.980] Hurry boy' she's waiting there for you\n[03:18.470] It's gonna take a lot to drag me away from you\n[03:24.980] There's nothing that a hundred men or more could ever do\n[03:30.200] I bless the rains down in Africa' I bless the rains down in Africa\n[03:40.640] I bless the rains down in Africa' I bless the rains down in Africa\n[03:50.960] I bless the rains down in Africa\n[03:56.240] Gonna take some time to do the things we never had",
