        "externalUrl": "",
        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:03.561] Midnight on a southern highway \n[00:27.107] Don't know if I'm going the right way\n[00:29.427] I haven't seen a single sign for miles\n[00:32.516] All this stormy weather  keeping us from being together\n[00:36.516] How long has it been since I've seen your smile \n[00:41.456] In this tunnel called the night  I can finally see a light\n[00:44.966] I've got a burning deep inside\n[00:49.016] I thought you might understand  I'm drivin' fast as I can\n[00:53.126] And you said  you'd wait for me\n[00:56.386] Goin' home  'cause I've been away much too long\n[01:03.675] Goin' home  going back to the place where my heart belongs\n[01:11.614] Goin' home  going back where I left my family\n[01:19.623] Goin' home and I hope that they're still waitin' there for me\n[01:28.073] In the eyes of the legal tender \n[01:44.409] You're the one who must surrender\n[01:46.079] I think  they call it responsibility\n[01:50.669] I'm a man in motion with only one compulsion\n[01:54.418] I've got to follow these dreams inside my heart\n[01:58.308] I'm not looking for a fight  no one's wrong and no one's right\n[02:02.338] Maybe we all need time apart\n[02:06.317] So please  understand  I'm doin' the best that I can\n[02:10.507] And you said  you'd wait for me\n[02:13.927] Goin' home  'cause I've been away much too long\n[02:20.976] Goin' home  going back to the place where my heart belongs\n[02:29.536] Goin' home  going back where I left my sanity\n[02:37.216] Goin' home and I hope that it's still waitin' there for me\n[02:45.456] I thought you might understand\n[03:35.317] I'm drivin' fast as I can\n[03:36.717] And you said you'd wait for me\n[03:41.566] Goin' home  'cause I've been away much too long\n[03:47.286] Goin' home  going back to the place where my heart belongs\n[03:55.296] Goin' home  going back where I left my family\n[04:03.406] Goin' home and I hope that they're still waitin' there for me\n[04:11.995] Goin' home  goin' home  goin' home  goin' home",
