        "fullLyrics": "[00:42.366] I heard about a man walkin' on the water\n[00:49.484] He had hope in his eyes\n[00:55.541] He didn't wear a crown or have any money\n[01:02.547] He didn't have any lies\n[01:09.214] He had holes in his pockets\n[01:15.686] He had holes in his hands\n[01:21.874] He looked like an outlaw talkin' to his lover\n[01:28.808] He was a spiritual man\n[01:48.301] I wanna be a prince not a king or a warrior\n[01:54.284] I wanna have a special light in my eyes\n[02:01.061] Wanna climb up a mountain find a tree of wisdom\n[02:07.851] I wanna feel good when I cry\n[02:14.421] And maybe someday I could be a teacher\n[02:20.991] I want that karma when you touch my hand\n[02:26.869] I'll walk through the streets\n[02:28.582] Talking to the homeless in winter\n[02:34.133] I wanna be a spiritual man yeah\n[02:53.610] I heard about a man who was born in the desert\n[03:00.831] He rode for days and nights across the sand\n[03:07.540] And one day he came upon an angel\n[03:12.795] The angel said hey you you're gonna be a spiritual man\n[03:46.031] Last night I saw a man walkin' toward a club in harlem\n[03:53.461] He had a black case in his hands\n[03:59.671] Went through the back door and pulled out his gold companion\n[04:04.498] He closed his eyes and played all night long like a self taught spiritual man",
