        "fullLyrics": "[00:16.691] Can you tell me where I might find the Hydra\n[00:20.581] Is he wearing a familiar face\n[00:24.631] Does he still live below Seventh Avenue\n[00:28.641] With the princess dipped in lace\n[00:34.821] Does he know that I'm a soldier of fortune\n[00:38.651] And not a victim of circumstance\n[00:42.831] We drew lots for his soft underbelly\n[00:46.811] Now his fate is sealed with my lance\n[01:02.431] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[01:05.261] You've never seen the man with nothing to say\n[01:10.360] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[01:13.160] You'd better watch yourself\n[01:15.060] St  George is on his way\n[01:27.809] Is it true that he's a mighty warrior\n[01:31.359] And a viper of the first degree\n[01:35.299] I've been sentenced here to slay the giant\n[01:39.278] Geld this fear I cannot see\n[01:54.717] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[01:57.397] You've never seen the man with nothing to say\n[02:02.647] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[02:05.357] You'd better watch yourself  St  George is on his way\n[02:49.205] Can you tell me where I might find the Hydra \n[02:53.125] Is he wearing a familiar face \n[02:57.365] Does he still live below Seventh Avenue\n[03:01.255] In the slums of Satan's grace \n[03:16.645] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[03:19.305] You've never seen the man with nothing to say\n[03:24.505] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[03:27.205] You'd better watch yourself  St  George is on his way\n[03:32.585] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[03:35.185] You've never seen the man with nothing to say\n[03:40.295] I can tell by the look in your eye\n[03:43.095] You'd better watch yourself  St  George is on his way\n[03:48.455] I can tell by the  I can tell by the\n[03:52.115] I can tell by the  I can tell by the\n[03:58.035] I can tell by the  I can tell by the\n[04:03.964] I can tell by the look in your eye",
