        "externalUrl": "",
        "favorite": false,
        "fullLyrics": "[00:20.670] You got a fast car\n[00:23.070] I want a ticket to anywhere\n[00:25.380] Maybe we make a deal\n[00:27.660] Maybe together we can get somewhere\n[00:30.090] Anyplace is better\n[00:32.250] Starting from zero got nothing to lose\n[00:34.680] Maybe we'll make something\n[00:36.660] But me myself I got nothing to prove\n[00:48.630] You got a fast car\n[00:50.880] And I got a plan to get us out of here\n[00:52.980] I been working at the convenience store\n[00:55.500] Managed to save just a little bit of money\n[00:57.630] We won't have to drive too far\n[00:59.910] Just 'cross the border and into the city\n[01:02.490] You and I can both get jobs\n[01:04.680] And finally see what it means to be living\n[01:15.960] You see my old man's got a problem\n[01:18.540] He live with the bottle that's the way it is\n[01:20.610] He says his body's too old for working\n[01:22.950] I say his body's too young to look like his\n[01:25.380] My mama went off and left him\n[01:27.660] She wanted more from life than he could give\n[01:29.700] I said somebody's got to take care of him\n[01:32.190] So I quit school and that's what I did\n[01:43.920] You got a fast car\n[01:45.960] But is it fast enough so we can fly away\n[01:48.570] We gotta make a decision\n[01:50.820] We leave tonight or live and die this way\n[02:01.080] I remember we were driving driving in your car\n[02:04.560] The speed so fast I felt like I was drunk\n[02:07.140] City lights lay out before us\n[02:09.060] And your arm felt nice wrapped 'round my shoulder\n[02:11.370] And I had a feeling that I belonged\n[02:15.990] And I had feeling I could be someone' be someone' be someone\n[02:32.250] You got a fast car\n[02:34.500] And we go cruising to entertain ourselves\n[02:36.810] You still ain't got a job\n[02:38.910] And I work in a market as a checkout girl\n[02:41.550] I know things will get better\n[02:43.800] You'll find work and I'll get promoted\n[02:46.140] We'll move out of the shelter\n[02:48.390] Buy a big house and live in the suburbs\n[02:58.710] I remember we were driving driving in your car\n[03:02.160] The speed so fast I felt like I was drunk\n[03:04.710] City lights lay out before us\n[03:06.600] And your arm felt nice wrapped 'round my shoulder\n[03:08.910] And I had a feeling that I belonged\n[03:13.530] And I had feeling I could be someone' be someone' be someone\n[03:29.730] You got a fast car\n[03:31.920] And I got a job that pays all our bills\n[03:34.200] You stay out drinking late at the bar\n[03:36.330] See more of your friends than you do of your kids\n[03:38.880] I'd always hoped for better\n[03:40.860] Thought maybe together you and me would find it\n[03:43.380] I got no plans I ain't going nowhere\n[03:45.690] So take your fast car and keep on driving\n[03:55.890] I remember we were driving driving in your car\n[03:59.340] The speed so fast I felt like I was drunk\n[04:01.890] City lights lay out before us\n[04:03.810] And your arm felt nice wrapped 'round my shoulder\n[04:06.090] And I had a feeling that I belonged\n[04:10.680] And I had feeling I could be someone' be someone' be someone\n[04:26.790] You got a fast car\n[04:28.890] But is it fast enough so you can fly away\n[04:31.530] You gotta make a decision",
