        "fullLyrics": "[00:12.082] Now that she's back in the atmosphere\n[00:15.259] With drops of Jupiter in her hair\n[00:24.267] She acts like summer and walks like rain\n[00:27.251] Reminds me that there's time to change\n[00:36.320] Since the return of her stay on the moon\n[00:39.114] She listens like spring and she talks like June\n[00:48.500] But tell me did you sail across the sun\n[00:52.643] Did you make it to the Milky Way\n[00:55.004] To see the lights all faded\n[00:57.866] And that heaven is overrated\n[01:00.497] And tell me did you fall for a shooting star\n[01:05.188] One without a permanent scar\n[01:07.040] And did you miss me\n[01:08.856] While you were looking for yourself out there\n[01:24.354] Now that she's back from that soul vacation\n[01:27.774] Tracing her way through the constellation\n[01:36.468] She checks out Mozart while she does Tae Bo\n[01:39.355] Reminds me that there's room to grow\n[01:48.645] Now that she's back in the atmosphere\n[01:51.175] I'm afraid that she might think of me as plain ol' Jane\n[01:55.893] Told a story about a man who is too afraid to fly\n[01:58.913] So he never did land\n[02:00.599] But tell me did the wind sweep you off your feet\n[02:04.911] Did you finally get the chance\n[02:06.445] To dance along the light of day\n[02:10.077] And head back to the Milky Way\n[02:12.884] Tell me did Venus blow your mind\n[02:16.874] Was it everything you wanted to find\n[02:19.215] And did you miss me\n[02:20.930] While you were looking for yourself out there\n[02:35.563] Can you imagine no love\n[02:37.476] Pride deep-fried chicken\n[02:39.688] Your best friend always sticking up for you\n[02:45.968] Even when I know you're wrong\n[02:47.667] Can you imagine no first dance\n[02:50.093] Freeze dried romance five-hour phone conversation\n[02:54.781] The best soy latte that you ever had and me\n[03:00.711] But tell me did the wind sweep you off your feet\n[03:05.044] Did you finally get the chance\n[03:06.780] To dance along the light of day\n[03:10.348] And head back toward the Milky Way\n[03:12.829] And tell me did you sail across the sun\n[03:17.173] Did you make it to the Milky Way\n[03:19.367] To see the lights all faded\n[03:22.391] And that heaven is overrated\n[03:25.012] Tell me did you fall for a shooting star\n[03:29.665] One without a permanent scar\n[03:31.599] And did you miss me\n[03:33.390] While you were looking for yourself\n[03:37.216] Na na na\n[03:44.108] And did you finally get the chance\n[03:45.689] To dance along the light of day\n[03:49.289] Na na na\n[03:54.572] And did you fall for a shooting star\n[03:58.534] Fall for a shooting star\n[04:01.298] Na na na\n[04:06.721] And now you're lonely looking for yourself out there",
